description: I am the second owner of this great quality left hand guitar. The serial number is 11021278 and it was built in February, 2011. Overall, this guitar is in very good condition and I have kept it in a non smoking, humidity controlled environment. The CT4B electronics produce a great sound. Just a little wear near the back/bottom of the pick guard from where me hand rested.Used ones are selling in the $600 USD range, with the only Used Canadian on being $1000 CDN. title: Left Handed Baritone Acoustic Guitar - Alvarez ABT60 - Mint
description: This guitar is in mint condition. Bought new 5 months ago from Luthier Denis Laroque at Real Instruments, this instrument is perfectly set up and ready to play. The Alvarez ABT60 is highly rated afforadable baritone guitar. It plays great and I love it, but I'm selling to fund the purchase of an electric guitar. A baritone guitar is pitched between a dreadnought and acoustic bass to give you deep tones with easy playability. description: LA Music 905-271-0303 230 Lakeshore Rd.East Mississauga , ON L5G 1G7 *SPECIAL: Mention Kijiji and get a free Gig Bag!  Godin Guitars 5th Avenue Kingpin Cognac Burst P90 Left-Handed 037728The Godin 5th Avenue brings you back to a time when the archtop acoustic guitar reigned supreme. With the soul of a 1950’s archtop, the 5th Avenue is a true vintage spirit of yesterday with today’s level of modern playability. With more projection & volume in the low/mids than traditional archtop acoustic guitars, the dynamically rich tone of the 5th Avenue makes this sophisticated instrument a dream to play, but not a nightmare to pay for. The Godin 5th Avenue now makes the affordable North American archtop guitar a reality! From Alt-Country, Delta Blues, Slide, Jazz to Rock, the 5th Avenue can really deliver both acoustically and electrically. The new Godin Kingpin P90 single-coil pickup delivers all that classic, vintage tone with presence, clarity and a little attitude thrown in for good measure!Made from Canadian Wild Cherry, the body of the 5th Avenue features a molded arched top and back, as well as an adjustable bridge, classic f-holes, contoured high-gloss headstock, floating pickguard and cream binding. Also, the rustic beauty of its Custom Polished Finish creates a gorgeous satin sheen reminiscent of the French polish of the 19th century.	FeaturesCanadian Wild Cherry archtopCanadian Wild cherry back & sidesSilver Leaf maple neckContoured high-gloss black headstockCustom Polished Finish reminiscent of thefrench polish of the 19th centuryRosewood FingerboardAdjustable Tusq Bridge by GraphtechCream Binding1x Godin Kingpin P90 single-coil pickup1x Volume, 1x Tone16" (406 mm) fingerboard radius24.84" (630 mm) Scale1.72" (43,7 mm) nut widthColors: Black, Cognac Burst & Natural*Left-handed Cognac model available!

title: Jasmine Acoustic - Left Handed
description: Used Jasmine acoustic - S35 LH (left handed) in great condition. This has very recently had a full setup/new strings from my pro repair shop (joesguitar at shaw.ca). Only reason I'm selling is I'm a right handed player, but this is a very playable and decent instrument for any left handed player.Although this is what is considered a budget or entry level guitar (under $500), having the action set at the nut and bridge at the right height, and having level frets or no sharp fret ends, decent strings that are installed properly, etc - turns it into something that plays (and stays in tune) like a more expensive model. Most new acoustics, not just Asian built, need some or all of those things adjusted. And the repairs to even a new or "like new" guitar could easily turn a "deal" into a different equation. This one's already done for you. I got it for free, and I'm passing along the savings. Sorry, I don't have a case though.If the ad is up, it's still available.

title: PRS SE Torero Grey Black
description: PRS SE Torero Grey Black w tremolo arm, soft PRS case Strap peg was moved to lower horn for left handed play. Strings however remain in Standard Right handed configuration. INFO Continuing the Paul Reed Smith legacy, the SE Torero takes two giant steps toward bridging the gap between the highly-acclaimed PRS SE series and their premier solidbody masterpieces. The minimalist fretboard free of inlays offsets the beauty of the SE Torero's flame maple top. Underneath, solid mahogany flanks a neck though body that leads all the way up an ultra-fast 25-1/2" 24-fret wide-thin neck. Its highly glossy body, neck, and headstock are all bound for a truly polished look and feel. But it's the accoutrements that set the SE Torero apart from other SE models. The PRS SE Torero's dressed to play with the big boys. Featuring two super-hot EMG pickups, this beautiful guitar is ready to tear it up — perfect for classic rock leads and the maddening demands of modern metal. A genuine Floyd Rose tremolo complements its wide thin neck and EMG picks, making the Torero a dream guitar for any guitarist with a vividly aggressive playing style or penchant for taking the spotlight. And any guitarist will appreciate the smooth feel and fine response of this masterfully crafted instrument. Paul Reed Smith SE Torero Features: Gray black finish Mahogany body with flame maple veneer Bound body, neck & headstock 25-1/2" scale length 24-fret maple wide-thin neck Neck-through body Ebony fretboard with no inlays Floyd Rose tremolo EMG 81 & 85 pickups Volume & tone control 3-way toggle Comes with a cordura gig bag

title: Martin LXM Acoustic LEFT HAND Guitar, Pristine
description: I'm offering a very special guitar rarely available preowned in left hand. Wonderful amazing tone guitar in a smaller package. Just recently bought this from a woman with arthritis in her hands. My purpose was I wanted something to be able to carry on a plane and stowe in the cabin. Problem was I guess I should of tried it a little longer but my old retired male hands are a little too large for the scale in the smaller frets close to the guitar body. That with the lack of scale for my playing style poses a problem. So regrettably I need to let her go. I say that because the tone is wonderful. One of the most comfortable instruments I have ever played by far. This would be suited for a male with smaller hands than I or better finger dexterity,woman or someone's aspiring child but note it is a fine instrument not a first time banger.. It is in mint condition and has had little to no play on it. Comes with a backpack style instrument bag nicely embroidered with the C.F.Martin logo. Large storage pocket, neck tether to keep it stable,padded base and both carry handle and backpack straps. This is certainly Martin class for sure. I know I own another Martin.If you notice most other guitars are compared to a Martin for a very good reason,tone... Silly offers will be ignored. It's a deal for someone for sure. My lose your gain.

title: Epiphone SG Standard Pro in Cherry - Left-Handed
description: LA Music905-271-0303230 Lakeshore Rd.EastMississauga , ON L5G 1G7Epiphone SG Standard Pro in Cherry - Left-HandedEpiphone honors the historic SG, one of the most original designs in rock, with the G-400 PRO, which now features Alnico Classic PRO pickups and push/pull coil-tapping. The original SG not only rivaled guitars of its own era for sonic variety but also proved to be a sign of things to come. Scores of rock, hard rock and metal guitarists embraced the original SG and made it a classic. Now, the G-400 PRO gives you the sound of a true SG without the vintage price tag and with the added tonal variety that youve come to expect from Epiphone.The G-400 PRO is inspired by the late 60s era SGs, both a players and collectors favorite, and uses the same dimensions and build techniques as vintage SGs made in the Kalamazoo, Michigan, factory during that classic era. The solid, tone-rich mahogany carved body gives the guitar a balanced feel on stage and in the studio (unlike cheap imitations that tend to be neck-heavy). The new Wilkinson Vintage Classic tuners are also lighter weight, which makes your G-400 PRO feel perfectly balanced on stage and in the studio. The SlimTaper "D" profile mahogany neck has a 24.75" scale with 24 frets and a 12 radius for incredible reach thanks to the SGs classic cutaway. And for that one-of-a-kind SG feel, the G-400 has a rosewood fingerboard with a 1.68 nut and pearloid trapezoid inlays. The truss rod cover is the classic Kalamazoo bell shape with SG PRO in white.Alnico Classic PR Power PickupsEpiphone always finds a way to make improvements on our classic designs and the G-400 PRO is no exception. Now featuring Epiphone Alnico Classic PRO 4-wire humbuckers in the neck and bridge positions, the G-400 PRO offers a tonal palette that far exceeds any other guitar of its kind. The Alnico Classic PROs feature Alnico V magnets for terrific humbucker sustain with a huge dynamic range that can go from clean to crunch at a touch. And now, the G-400 PRO features coil-tapping on both pickups via a push/pull control on the pickups volume controls.FeaturesBody - MahoganyNeck - Mahogany, glued-inScale - 24.75"Neck Profile - SlimTaper "D"Nut width - 1.68Fingerboard - rosewood with trapezoid inlaysFrets - 22, medium jumboFingerboard Radius - 12"Trussrod cover - SG PRONut - black imitation bone (PVC)Neck Pickup - Epiphone Alnico Classic PRO 4-wire humbuckerBridge Pickup - Epiphone Alnico Classic PRO 4-wire humbuckerBridge - LockTone Tune-o-maticTailpiece - LockTone StopbarControls - Epiphone all-metal 3-way pickup selector. Volume and tone controls feature full-size 500K O potentiometers-Neck pickup volume with push/pull coil-tapping-Bridge pickup volume with push/pull coil-tapping-Neck pickup tone-Bridge pickup toneHardware - NickelMachine Heads - Wilkinson Vintage Classics, 14:1 ratioColor - Cherry

description: I'm offering a very special guitar rarely available in left hand. Wonderful amazing tone guitar in a smaller package. Just recently bought this but from a woman with arthritis in her hands. My purpose was I wanted something to be able to carry on a plane and stowe in the cabin. Problem was I guess I should of tried it a little longer but my old retired male hands are a little too large for the scale in the smaller frets close to the guitar body. That with the lack of scale for my playing style poses a problem. So regrettably I need to let her go. I say that because the tone is wonderful. One of the most comfortable instruments I have ever played by far. This would be suited fr a smaller male,woman or someones aspiring child. It is in mint condition and has had little to no play on it. Comes with a backpack style instrument bag nicely embroidered with the C.F.Martin logo. I know I own another Martin.If you notice most other guitars are compared to a Martin for a very good reason,tone... Silly offers will be ignored. It's a deal for someone for sure. My lose your gain.

title: CTS 250K Reverse Audio Taper Pot for Lefty Guitar
description: CTS EP4385LThese are 250K reverse audio taper potentiometers manufactured by CTS for left handed electric guitar circuits. If you need to replace a volume or tone control in a lefty guitar with single-coil pickups then this is probably what you need.Sized to fit a 3/8" diameter mounting hole on a plastic pickguard or metal control plate. Each one comes with a set of mounting hardware that includes a flat washer, lock washer and a hex mounting nut.These are the highest quality left handed potentiometers that we can locate. They are an excellent replacement part for most left handed guitars with single-coil pickups.Send us a message to arrange a visit, or to ask us any questions.
